"></a></h2><h2>Kitchen Measuring Conversions</h2></div><div><p>Converting k=
itchen measurements is crucial for multiplying or cutting a recipe down. Wh=
ether you're converting ounces to cups or teaspoons to tablespoons, we have=
 you covered! Check out our list of common kitchen measuring conversions wi=
thin the US imperial system below. If you're looking for conversions to the=
 metric system, use our guide for <a href=3D"https://www.webstaurantstore.c=
om/article/212/cooking-conversion-chart.html" target=3D"_blank"><strong>US =
to metric cooking conversions</strong></a>.</p>

<h3>Liquid Measurement Conversions</h3>

<div class=3D"image pull-right"><img src=3D"https://cdnimg.webstaurantstore=
.com/images/products/large/401170/1486575.jpg" style=3D"width: 300px" alt=
=3D"A liquid measuring cup set with each cup filled with various liquids"><=
/div>

<p>Use the following liquid measurement conversions to easily adjust your r=
ecipes.</p>

<ul class=3D"highlights"><li class=3D"icon-check">1 fluid ounce =3D 2 table=
spoons</li>
<li class=3D"icon-check">1 cup =3D 8 fluid ounces</li>
<li class=3D"icon-check">1 pint =3D 2 cups or 16 fluid ounces</li>
<li class=3D"icon-check">1 quart =3D 2 pints or 32 fluid ounces</li>
<li class=3D"icon-check">1 gallon =3D 4 quarts or 128 fluid ounces</li></ul=
>

<h3>Dry Measurement Conversions</h3>

<p>Use the following dry measurement conversions to easily adjust your reci=
pes.</p>

<ul class=3D"highlights"><li class=3D"icon-check">1 tablespoon =3D 3 teaspo=
ons</li>
<li class=3D"icon-check">1/4 cup =3D 4 tablespoons</li>
<li class=3D"icon-check">1/3 cup =3D 5 tablespoons + 1 teaspoon</li>
<li class=3D"icon-check">1/2 cup =3D 8 tablespoons</li>
<li class=3D"icon-check">1 cup =3D 16 tablespoons</li></ul>

<h3>Order of Measuring Cups</h3>

<p>Many measuring cups and spoons come in <a href=3D"https://www.webstauran=
tstore.com/2925/measuring-cups-spoons.html?filter=3Dtype:measuring-cup-sets=
:measuring-spoon-sets&amp;multi=3Dtrue" target=3D"_blank"><strong>measuring=
 spoon and cup sets</strong></a>, but it still can be helpful to know the o=
rder of measuring cups by size when converting recipes. The standard measur=
ing cup sizes in cooking from smallest to largest are 1/8 cup, 1/4 cup, 1/3=
 cup, 1/2 cup, and 1 cup. Similarly, the standard measuring spoon sizes in =
cooking from smallest to largest are 1/4 teaspoon, 1/2 teaspoon, 1 teaspoon=
, 1/2 tablespoon, and 1 tablespoon.</p></div></div></div><div class=3D"guid=
e-section-group"><div class=3D"guide-section"><div><h2><a id=3D"chart"></a>=
</h2><h2>Kitchen Measurements Chart</h2></div><div><p>Use our <a href=3D"ht=
